HEADWORD: Ilio-
<hw>Il"i*o-</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[From <er>Ilium</er>.]</ety> <def>A
combining form used in anatomy to denote <xex>connection with</xex>, or
<xex>relation to</xex>, <xex>the ilium</xex>; <as>as,
<ex>ilio</ex>-femoral, <ex>ilio</ex>-lumbar, <ex>ilio</ex>-psoas,
etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

